<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Wang_Juzheng%27s_Spinning_Wheel,_Close_Up_2.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
<i>The Spinning Wheel</i>, by <a href="/wiki/Song_Dynasty" title="Song Dynasty">Northern Song</a> (960–1127) artist Wang Juzheng; the Chinese invented the <a href="/wiki/Belt_(mechanical)" title="Belt (mechanical)">belt drive</a> by the 1st century BC for silk <a href="/wiki/Quilling" title="Quilling">quilling</a> devices. This was essential for the invention of the later <a href="/wiki/Spinning_wheel" title="Spinning wheel">spinning wheel</a>, the latter invented in either <a href="/wiki/China" title="China">China</a> or <a href="/wiki/India" title="India">India</a> around the 11th century and was first mentioned in <a href="/wiki/Europe" title="Europe">Europe</a> in the statutes of a guild at <a href="/wiki/Speyer" title="Speyer">Speyer</a>, <a href="/wiki/Germany" title="Germany">Germany</a> in about 1280.<sup id="cite_ref-171" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-171" title=""><span>[</span>172<span>]</span></a></sup></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Chinese_Puddle_and_Blast_Furnace.jpg" class="image" title="A print illustration from an encyclopedia published in 1637 by Song Yingxing (1587–1666), showing two men working a blast furnace on the right and the puddling process on the left."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7f/Chinese_Puddle_and_Blast_Furnace.jpg/180px-Chinese_Puddle_and_Blast_Furnace.jpg" width="180" height="142" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
