<a href="/wiki/Guo_Shoujing" title="Guo Shoujing">Guo Shoujing</a> (1233–1316) established a calendar in 1281 which measured a year in roughly the same length as the Western <a href="/wiki/Gregorian_calendar" title="Gregorian calendar">Gregorian calendar</a> of 1582</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Wuxing.svg" class="image" title="The wu xing, or Chinese Five Elements, with green representing wood and east, red representing fire and south, yellow representing earth and center, white representing metal and west, and black representing water and north"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/Wuxing.svg/180px-Wuxing.svg.png" width="180" height="180" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
