The endless power-transmitting <a href="/wiki/Chain_drive" title="Chain drive">chain drive</a> from <a href="/wiki/Su_Song" title="Su Song">Su Song</a>'s book of 1094 describing his <a href="/wiki/Clock_tower" title="Clock tower">clock tower</a><sup id="cite_ref-temple_1986_72_207-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-temple_1986_72-207" title=""><span>[</span>208<span>]</span></a></sup></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Bellows_(PSF).svg" class="image" title="Bellows were used not only in metallurgy by the ancient Chinese, but also in chemical warfare."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/83/Bellows_%28PSF%29.svg/180px-Bellows_%28PSF%29.svg.png" width="180" height="195" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Bellows_(PSF).svg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
<a href="/wiki/Bellows" title="Bellows">Bellows</a> were used not only in <a href="/wiki/History_of_ferrous_metallurgy" title="History of ferrous metallurgy">metallurgy</a> by the ancient Chinese, but also in <a href="/wiki/Chemical_warfare" title="Chemical warfare">chemical warfare</a>.</div>
